Thromboembolic events occurred in 28 of 362 closed cases for a rate of 7.7% (95%CI 5.4%–11.0%) among closed cases, corresponding to a cumulative rate of 21.0%. Eight events occurred in ICU patients (16.7%; 95%CI 8.7%–29.6%) corresponding to a cumulative rate of 27.6%. Twenty events occurred in patients on the general ward (6.4%; 95%CI 4.2%–9.6%) corresponding to a cumulative rate of 6.6% (Table 3
). We reported a detailed description of all thromboembolic events in Table 4
.
